    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2003-01-22</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-11-28T17:35:40Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[State and Local Aid and Economic Stimulus Act of 2003 - Amends Federal law to authorize and make appropriations for FY 2003 for a one-time revenue grant to States and local governments.<p>Specifies amounts to be allotted to each of the States based upon population and changes in unemployment rates.<p>Declares the sense of Congress that priority for using funds allotted under this Act should be given to homeland security, medicaid, public health, highway construction, childcare, elementary, secondary, and higher education, and the prevention of additional property tax increases.]]></text>
      </summary>
